    <string name="diag_auto_display_title">AutoDisplayService (com.xdja.containerservice)</string>
    <string name="diag_auto_display_desc">Starts the Qt→VirtualDisplay service directly. This is Dilink5\'s internal mechanism: it retrieves the native Qt Surface of the cluster and passes it to createVirtualDisplay.</string>
    <string name="diag_btn_start_auto_display">START AutoDisplayService</string>
    <string name="diag_btn_stop">STOP</string>
    <string name="diag_fission_title">Fission Pipeline (cluster VirtualDisplay creation)</string>
    <string name="diag_fission_desc">Full sequence: sendInfo(30)+sendInfo(16) → Qt registers its Surface → am startservice AutoDisplayService → updateDisplay() → createVirtualDisplay(fission_testVirtualSurface). Then launches DashBoard on that display.</string>
    <string name="diag_btn_sendinf_java">☕ sendInfo Java Direct (v0.1.21)</string>
    <string name="diag_btn_fission_create">🚀 Create Fission Display</string>
    <string name="diag_btn_fission_launch">▶ Launch Dashboard</string>
    <string name="diag_s5_title">5. System Sniffer (Reverse Engineering)</string>
    <string name="diag_s5_desc">Captures logcat (all relevant tags) + periodic dumpsys snapshots into an exportable file. Designed for reverse engineering: intercepts display, SF, AM, WM, BYD, autoContainer, Qt, broadcasts.</string>
